clinical_study.brief_title: Non-interventional Observational Study With Pramipexole: Impact on Non-motor Symptoms in Parkinson's Disease
clinical_study.official_title: Non-motor Symptoms (Depressive Symptoms) of Parkinson's Disease and Their Course Under Pramipexole Treatment

brief_summary.textblock:
- To compare the effect of pramipexole on depressive symptoms in early and advanced PD patients
- To evaluate the course of depressive symptoms measured with UPDRS Part I (mentation, behavior and mood) and with HADS-D under pramipexole treatment
- To investigate whether improvement of depressive symptoms is linked to improvement in motor function (UPDRS Part III)

primary_outcome.measure: Improvement of depressive symptoms (UPDRS item 3, HADS-D) compared to baseline in early and advanced Parkinsons's disease
Change in sum scores of UPDRS Part III (motor examination) from baseline and UPDRS Part I (mentation, behavior and mood) from baseline
Change in HADS subscores (anxiety and depression) from baseline

secondary_outcome.measure: Baseline pattern of patient rated symptom list (HADS)
Correlation of the change in UPDRS Part I and UPDRS Part III at the final visit

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion criteria:
1. Idiopathic Parkinsons disease with or without fluctuations
2. Indication for treatment with Sifrol®
3. Male or female patients of age
4. Presence of at least mild depressive symptoms (as judged by the treating physician)
5. Ability to reliably complete a self-rating scale (HADS)
Exclusion criteria:
1. Any contraindications according to the Summary of Product Characteristics (SPC): hypersensitivity to pramipexole or to any of the excipients.
2. Ongoing treatment with Sifrol®.
